To obtain an in-depth understanding of the energy storage behaviors, we carry out the CV scans of the SnO2[O]rTiO2-PGN, Ad-SnO2-G, and Ana-SnO2-PGN anodes under various speeds (0.1–10 mV s−1), as shown in Fig. 5a–c. The purpose of analyzing the Ad-SnO2-G anode is to demonstrate the influences of electrochemical kinetics from the PGN phase. Similarly, we intend to reveal the contribution of Ad rTiO2 in SnO2[O]rTiO2-PGN by comparing the electrochemical behavior of SnO2[O]rTiO2-PGN and Ana-SnO2-PGN. As the scan rate increases from 0.1 to 10 mV s−1, the shapes of each sample’s CV patterns are similar and exhibit broad lithiation and delithiation peaks. Based on the expression of the power law, the current response (i, mA) of the CV scan correlates with the value of scan rate (v, mV s−1) and follows the specific formula, as shown in Eq. (1):45Figure 5
